  <p>Block 2 introduces the three core surface processes — <strong>weathering</strong>, <strong>erosion</strong>, and <strong>deposition</strong> — and asks students to distinguish them in real photographs. Bell ringer: match each process to its action ("breaks rock down" / "moves material" / "drops material in a new place"). Exit: predict where deposition will occur in a teacher-supplied landscape image and explain why.</p>
